	<strong>Hi everyone</strong>,
	<p>I'm Vignesh (Final year ECE), one of the contributors of  'course'. This is the story of the app, it all began during the NASA 2013 hackathon. We had a request from the director for a student-faculty interaction app. Shiva Nandan (aka seek), my delta senior disucussed with me about the app during our journey. He had already developed a prototype with very basic feature, the app with its partially finished features was already impressive, it looked if he had already completed the app, he wanted someone to work on the app the rest of the app and complete it. Usually when a project is proposed in delta, members volutier to the project. The problem with this app was that he built the prototype with the then  new technologies which no one in the club has worked on so we were reluctant to take up the task. I was jobless after pragyan so I voluntired and promised to complete it during summer vacations. </p>
	<p>Finally due to the tough competion that I faced while getting a summer intern and the fact that I come from a non compsci branch  made me fear that spending time on the app would affect my career. Sadly I dropped out of the app and did my intern and the development process remained idle for about 6 months. </p>
	<p>I resumed my work in late October,2013. I was refactoring code and redesigned the database schema and was passively contributing, but I was keen on pursuading some of my batch mates and juniors to work on the app. The development work gained friction just before my semester exam, I'm still not sure if my lack of interest in ECE or the fun in building something caused it. After spending my entire winter holdidays on the app, here it is.</p>

